But imagine for a moment that Warren’s federal child-care program could indeed be paid for, and that fretting over cost control is a hateful exercise.
In short order, Quebec families flocked to the new program, including many who had previously relied on more informal child-care arrangements.
Its designers were serious, thoughtful people who wanted to do right by Quebec families, yet their experiment had decidedly mixed results.
Warren’s proposed federal child-care program would do nothing for stay-at-home mothers and fathers.
Judging by her child-care proposal, that Warren has been replaced by someone else entirely.